<item>
            <title>[FLINK-14300] StreamTask#invoke leaks threads if OperatorChain fails to be constructed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-14300</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In the&#160;&lt;b&gt;StreamTask#invoke&lt;/b&gt; method if an exception occurs during the allocation of the &lt;a href=&quot;#L370]&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;operatorChain&lt;/a&gt; class, the &lt;a href=&quot;#L485-L491]&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;noopener&quot;&gt;exception handling&lt;/a&gt; fails to cleanup the threads allocated as&#160;&lt;b&gt;StreamTask#recordWriters&lt;/b&gt;. This causes threads to leak as flink attempts to continually restart and fail for the same cause.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;An example cause is a deserialization issue on a custom operator from a checkpoint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached is a suggested fix for the master branch.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
